ngitudinally arranged fibers are continuous with the smooth muscle present in the mesosalpinx.\" [https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/B9780721693231500106, https://www.pathologyoutlines.com/topic/fallopiantubesnormal.html, https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3414]\n+intersection_of: UBERON:0006642 ! muscle layer of oviduct\n+intersection_of: part_of UBERON:0003889 ! fallopian tube\n+relationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7655-4833 ! Ellen Quardokus\n+relationship: term_tracker_item https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3414\n+created_by: dragon-ai-agent\n+property_value: dcterms-date \"2026-05-17T00:00:00Z\" xsd:dateTime\n+\n+[Term]\n+id: UBERON:8600127\n+name: antimesosalpinx muscularus\n+def: \"A muscular layer in the antimesosalpinx region of the fallopian tube. The muscular layer of the fallopian tube consists primarily of an inner layer of circularly arranged muscle fibers covered by an outer layer of longitudinally oriented fibers, and these longitudinally arranged fibers are continuous with the smooth muscle present in the mesosalpinx.\" [https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/B9780721693231500106, https://vanat.ahc.umn.edu/ungDissect/Lab17/Lab17.html, https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3414]\n+intersection_of: UBERON:0006642 ! muscle layer of oviduct\n+intersection_of: part_of UBERON:0003889 ! fallopian tube\n+relationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7655-4833 ! Ellen Quardokus\n+relationship: term_tracker_item https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3414\n+created_by: dragon-ai-agent\n+property_value: dcterms-date \"2026-05-17T00:00:00Z\" xsd:dateTime\n+\n+[Term]\n+id: UBERON:8600128\n+name: superior epithelium\n+def: \"An epithelium in the superior region of the mucosa of fallopian tube.\" [https://www.pathologyoutlines.com/topic/fallopiantubesnormal.html, https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3414]\n+intersection_of: UBERON:0000483 ! epithelium\n+intersec