urface of lymphoid follicles in gut-associated lymphoid tissue. It is found in Peyer's patches of the small intestine and appendix in humans and in the intestine and caecal patches in mice. This layer contains specialised M cells and has fewer goblet cells compared to surrounding tissue. This layer plays a crucial role in mucosal immune surveillance.\" [DOI:10.1007/s00702-022-02561-x, DOI:10.4061/2010/823710]\n224847: synonym: \"FAE\" EXACT [DOI:10.1007/s00702-022-02561-x]\n224848: is_a: UBERON:0004693 ! Peyer's patch epithelium\n224849: relationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0009-0005-7919-4905\n224850: property_value: dcterms-date \"2024-11-07T11:44:27Z\" xsd:dateTime\n224851: \n224852: [Term]\n224853: id: UBERON:8700002\n\n(Showing lines 224744-224853 of 226194. Use offset=224854 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"relationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2025-02-24T14:15:29Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600124\nname: mesosalpinx epithelium\ndef: \"An epithelium in the mesosalpinx region of the mucosa of fallopian tube.\" [https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3414, https://www.pathologyoutlines.com/topic/fallopiantubesnormal.html]\nintersection_of: UBERON:0000483 ! epithelium\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:0005048 ! mucosa of fallopian tube\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7655-4833 ! Ellen Quardokus\nrelationship: term_tracker_item https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3414\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2026-05-17T00:00:00Z\" xsd:dateTime\ncreated_by: dragon-ai-agent\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600125\nname: antimesosalpinx epithelium\ndef: \"An epithelium in the antimesosalpinx region of the mucosa of fallopian tube.\" [https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3414, https://vanat.ahc.umn.edu/ungDissect/Lab17/Lab17.html, https://www.pathologyoutlines.com/topic/fallopiantubesnormal.html]\nintersection_of: UBERON