{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778979277727,"sessionID":"ses_1cc98b089ffeqDgg64MacYW8kG","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_An7Td4NgwLWhaX032q3BdB6V","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+Implemented the requested regional fallopian tube tissue-layer additions and committed the ontology changes locally. Changes committed in PR #<NN>.\n+\n+Summary:\n+- added mesosalpinx epithelium\n+- added antimesosalpinx epithelium\n+- added mesosalpinx muscularus\n+- added antimesosalpinx muscularus\n+- added superior and inferior regional epithelium terms for fallopian tube\n+- added superior and inferior regional muscular layer terms for fallopian tube\n+\n+I followed the later curator clarification in the issue comments that expanded the request to eight total terms and clarified that these are regional designations within fallopian tube tissue layers rather than literal parts of the mesosalpinx membrane itself.\n*** Add File: PR_COMMENTS.md\n+This change addresses issue `#3414` by adding the seven missing regional fallopian tube tissue-layer terms requested in the issue discussion, alongside the already-existing `UBERON:8600117 antimesosalpinx` term.\n+\n+Added terms:\n+- `UBERON:8600124` mesosalpinx epithelium\n+- `UBERON:8600125` antimesosalpinx epithelium\n+- `UBERON:8600126` mesosalpinx muscularus\n+- `UBERON:8600127` antimesosalpinx muscularus\n+- `UBERON:8600128` superior epithelium of fallopian tube\n+- `UBERON:8600129` inferior epithelium of fallopian tube\n+- `UBERON:8600130` superior muscular layer of fallopian tube\n+- `UBERON:8600131` inferior muscular layer of fallopian tube\n+\n+Rationale:\n+- The original issue body asked for mesosalpinx and antimesosalpinx regional terms.\n+- Later curator comments clarified that the needed scope is eight total terms, including superior and inferior regional epithelium and muscular layer terms.\n+- The same comments also clarified that these labels refer to regional polarity within fallopian tube mucosa or muscle layer, not to structures that are directly part of the mesosalpinx membrane itself.\n+- To keep labels anatomically explicit, the superior/inferior primary names were expanded to include `of fallopian tube`, while preserving the requested shorter labels as exact synonyms where relevant.\n+\n+Modeling notes:\n+- epithelial regional terms were modeled as `epithelium` that are `part_of` `mucosa of fallopian tube` (`UBERON:0005048`)\n+- muscular regional terms were modeled as `muscle layer of oviduct` that are `part_of` `fallopian tube` (`UBERON:0003889`)\n+- all new terms include contributor attribution, tracker link, `created_by`, and `dcterms-date`\n+\n+Sources used for definitions and scope:\n+- issue `#3414` body and comments\n+- Pathology Outlines fallopian tube histology page for mucosal and muscle-layer context\n+- University of Minnesota anatomy page for the antimesosalpinx definition\n+- ScienceDirect reproductive anatomy text for the myosalpinx / muscular-layer description and continuity with mesosalpinx smooth muscle\n+\n+Validation performed:\n+- reviewed existing UBERON terms for `mesosalpinx`, `antimesosalpinx`, `mucosa of fallopian tube`, and `muscle layer of oviduct`\n+- confirmed the proposed new labels were not already present\n+- used the standard `obo-checkout.pl` / `obo-checkin.pl` workflow\n+- reserialized `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo` with `robot convert`\n+- reviewed the final ontology diff and scoped the commit to the intended ontology file only\n+\n+Checklist completed:\n+- [x] read imported issue context and comments\n+- [x] checked existing related UBERON terms\n+- [x] determined final scope from latest curator guidance\n+- [x] added all missing requested terms with metadata\n+- [x] checked terms into `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`\n+- [x] reserialized the ontology file\n+- [x] committed only the ontology file\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\nA PR_COMMENTS.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,11 @@\n+Implemented the requested regional fallopian tube tissue-layer additions and committed the ontology changes locally. Changes committed in PR #<NN>.\n+\n+Summary:\n+- added mesosalpinx epithelium\n+- added antimesosalpinx epithelium\n+- added mesosalpinx muscularus\n+- added antimesosalpinx muscularus\n+- added superior and inferior regional epithelium terms for fallopian tube\n+- added superior and inferior regional muscular layer terms for fallopian tube\n+\n+I followed the later curator clarification in the issue comments that expanded the request to eight total terms and clarified that these are regional designations within fallopian tube tissue layers rather than literal parts of the mesosalpinx membrane itself.\n\nIndex: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,44 @@\n+This change addresses issue `#3414` by adding the seven missing regional fallopian tube tissue-layer terms requested in the issue discussion, alongside the already-existing `UBERON:8600117 antimesosalpinx` term.\n+\n+Added terms:\n+- `UBERON:8600124` mesosalpinx epithelium\n+- `UBERON:8600125` antimesosalpinx epithelium\n+- `UBERON:8600126` mesosalpinx muscularus\n+- `UBERON:8600127` antimesosalpinx muscularus\n+- `UBERON:8600128` superior epithelium of fallopian tube\n+- `UBERON:8600129` inferior epithelium of fallopian tube\n+- `UBERON:8600130` superior muscular layer of fallopian tube\n+- `UBERON:8600131` inferior muscular layer of fallopian tube\n+\n+Rationale:\n+- The original issue body asked for mesosalpinx and antimesosalpinx regional terms.\n+- Later curator comments clarified that the needed scope is eight total terms, including superior and inferior regional epithelium and muscular layer terms.\n+- The same comments also clarified that these labels refer to regional polarity within fallopian tube mucosa or muscle layer, not to structures that are directly part of the mesosalpinx membrane itself.\n+- To keep labels anatomically explicit, the superior/inferior primary names were expanded to include `of fallopian tube`, while preserving the requested shorter labels as exact synonyms where relevant.\n+\n+Modeling notes:\n+- epithelial regional terms were modeled as `epithelium` that are `part_of` `mucosa of fallopian tube` (`UBERON:0005048`)\n+- muscular regional terms were modeled as `muscle layer of oviduct` that are `part_of` `fallopian tube` (`UBERON:0003889`)\n+- all new terms include contributor attribution, tracker link, `created_by`, and `dcterms-date`\n+\n+Sources used for definitions and scope:\n+- issue `#3414` body and comments\n+- Pathology Outlines fallopian tube histology page for mucosal and muscle-layer context\n+- University of Minnesota anatomy page for the antimesosalpinx definition\n+- ScienceDirect reproductive anatomy text for the myosalpinx / muscular-layer description and continuity with mesosalpinx smooth muscle\n+\n+Validation performed:\n+- reviewed existing UBERON terms for `mesosalpinx`, `antimesosalpinx`, `mucosa of fallopian tube`, and `muscle layer of oviduct`\n+- confirmed the proposed new labels were not already present\n+- used the standard `obo-checkout.pl` / `obo-checkin.pl` workflow\n+- reserialized `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo` with `robot convert`\n+- reviewed the final ontology diff and scoped the commit to the intended ontology file only\n+\n+Checklist completed:\n+- [x] read imported issue context and comments\n+- [x] checked existing related UBERON terms\n+- [x] determined final scope from latest curator guidance\n+- [x] added all missing requested terms with metadata\n+- [x] checked terms into `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`\n+- [x] reserialized the ontology file\n+- [x] committed only the ontology file\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md","relativePath":"ISSUE_COMMENTS.md","type":"add","patch":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,11 @@\n+Implemented the requested regional fallopian tube tissue-layer additions and committed the ontology changes locally. Changes committed in PR #<NN>.\n+\n+Summary:\n+- added mesosalpinx epithelium\n+- added antimesosalpinx epithelium\n+- added mesosalpinx muscularus\n+- added antimesosalpinx muscularus\n+- added superior and inferior regional epithelium terms for fallopian tube\n+- added superior and inferior regional muscular layer terms for fallopian tube\n+\n+I followed the later curator clarification in the issue comments that expanded the request to eight total terms and clarified that these are regional designations within fallopian tube tissue layers rather than literal parts of the mesosalpinx membrane itself.\n","additions":11,"deletions":0},{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md","relativePath":"PR_COMMENTS.md","type":"add","patch":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,44 @@\n+This change addresses issue `#3414` by adding the seven missing regional fallopian tube tissue-layer terms requested in the issue discussion, alongside the already-existing `UBERON:8600117 antimesosalpinx` term.\n+\n+Added terms:\n+- `UBERON:8600124` mesosalpinx epithelium\n+- `UBERON:8600125` antimesosalpinx epithelium\n+- `UBERON:8600126` mesosalpinx muscularus\n+- `UBERON:8600127` antimesosalpinx muscularus\n+- `UBERON:8600128` superior epithelium of fallopian tube\n+- `UBERON:8600129` inferior epithelium of fallopian tube\n+- `UBERON:8600130` superior muscular layer of fallopian tube\n+- `UBERON:8600131` inferior muscular layer of fallopian tube\n+\n+Rationale:\n+- The original issue body asked for mesosalpinx and antimesosalpinx regional terms.\n+- Later curator comments clarified that the needed scope is eight total terms, including superior and inferior regional epithelium and muscular layer terms.\n+- The same comments also clarified that these labels refer to regional polarity within fallopian tube mucosa or muscle layer, not to structures that are directly part of the mesosalpinx membrane itself.\n+- To keep labels anatomically explicit, the superior/inferior primary names were expanded to include `of fallopian tube`, while preserving the requested shorter labels as exact synonyms where relevant.\n+\n+Modeling notes:\n+- epithelial regional terms were modeled as `epithelium` that are `part_of` `mucosa of fallopian tube` (`UBERON:0005048`)\n+- muscular regional terms were modeled as `muscle layer of oviduct` that are `part_of` `fallopian tube` (`UBERON:0003889`)\n+- all new terms include contributor attribution, tracker link, `created_by`, and `dcterms-date`\n+\n+Sources used for definitions and scope:\n+- issue `#3414` body and comments\n+- Pathology Outlines fallopian tube histology page for mucosal and muscle-layer context\n+- University of Minnesota anatomy page for the antimesosalpinx definition\n+- ScienceDirect reproductive anatomy text for the myosalpinx / muscular-layer description and continuity with mesosalpinx smooth muscle\n+\n+Validation performed:\n+- reviewed existing UBERON terms for `mesosalpinx`, `antimesosalpinx`, `mucosa of fallopian tube`, and `muscle layer of oviduct`\n+- confirmed the proposed new labels were not already present\n+- used the standard `obo-checkout.pl` / `obo-checkin.pl` workflow\n+- reserialized `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo` with `robot convert`\n+- reviewed the final ontology diff and scoped the commit to the intended ontology file only\n+\n+Checklist completed:\n+- [x] read imported issue context and comments\n+- [x] checked existing related UBERON terms\n+- [x] determined final scope from latest curator guidance\n+- [x] added all missing requested terms with metadata\n+- [x] checked terms into `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`\n+- [x] reserialized the ontology file\n+- [x] committed only the ontology file\n","additions":44,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\nA PR_COMMENTS.md","time":{"start":1778979277719,"end":1778979277726}},"id":"prt_e336d4a65001493GnJppS760Dx","sessionID":"ses_1cc98b089ffeqDgg64MacYW8kG","messageID":"msg_e336d0474001U6P7CKDH1VSZGo"}}
